From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rurix Godot Bridge <rurix@example.invalid>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 12:25:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Add a RENDER_TIMESTAMP bracket around the particles view-axis copy

Stacked on 0001..0029 + 0040..0046. Pure telemetry micro-patch: ParticlesStorage
::particles_set_view_axis() issues the view-axis fill-instances (and optional
sort) compute dispatches but, unlike the separate _particles_process "Update
GPUParticles" call site, had NO RENDER_TIMESTAMP, so that copy work was invisible
to the GPU profiler / RENDER_TIMESTAMP-driven per-pass timing.

Adds RENDER_TIMESTAMP("Particles View-Axis Copy") right after the two early-out
checks (wrong draw_order/transform_align, and particles-not-yet-processed) so it
brackets only frames that do the work, and closes it with the Godot "< "
region-end convention RENDER_TIMESTAMP("< Particles View-Axis Copy") at the end
of the function. No control-flow change, no new dispatch, no behavior change.
---
 .../renderer_rd/storage_rd/particles_storage.cpp          | 15 +++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+)

diff --git a/servers/rendering/renderer_rd/storage_rd/particles_storage.cpp b/servers/rendering/renderer_rd/storage_rd/particles_storage.cpp
index 512a9ee..c1dd994 100644
--- a/servers/rendering/renderer_rd/storage_rd/particles_storage.cpp
+++ b/servers/rendering/renderer_rd/storage_rd/particles_storage.cpp
@@ -1250,6 +1250,16 @@ void ParticlesStorage::particles_set_view_axis(RID p_particles, const Vector3 &p
 		return; //particles have not processed yet
 	}
 
+	// GRX telemetry (patch 0047): bracket the view-axis fill-instances copy work
+	// with a RENDER_TIMESTAMP. Unlike the "Update GPUParticles" process path (a
+	// different call site further down this file), particles_set_view_axis had no
+	// timestamp, so the copy/sort dispatches it issues were invisible to the GPU
+	// profiler / RENDER_TIMESTAMP-driven per-pass timing. Placed after the two
+	// early-out checks (wrong draw_order/transform_align and not-yet-processed) so
+	// it brackets only frames that actually do the work; pure telemetry, no control
+	// flow change.
+	RENDER_TIMESTAMP("Particles View-Axis Copy");
+
 	bool do_sort = particles->draw_order == RSE::PARTICLES_DRAW_ORDER_VIEW_DEPTH;
 
 	//copy to sort buffer
@@ -1438,6 +1448,11 @@ void ParticlesStorage::particles_set_view_axis(RID p_particles, const Vector3 &p
 	}
 
 	RD::get_singleton()->compute_list_end();
+
+	// GRX telemetry (patch 0047): close the "Particles View-Axis Copy" timestamp
+	// region opened above (the Godot "< " region-end convention, e.g.
+	// cluster_builder_rd.cpp "< Bake 3D Cluster").
+	RENDER_TIMESTAMP("< Particles View-Axis Copy");
 }
 
 void ParticlesStorage::_particles_update_buffers(Particles *particles) {
